# Core Engineering Standards

Applies to all implementation work in this repo.

- Use Node.js + Express.js + MongoDB patterns aligned with project docs.
- Use ES Modules only (`import`/`export`), no CommonJS.
- Keep code simple, explicit, and maintainable.
- Prefer `async/await`; avoid callback-style async.
- Never leave unhandled promises.
- Keep naming consistent:
  - variables/functions: `camelCase`
  - classes/models: `PascalCase`
  - constants: `UPPER_SNAKE_CASE`
- Keep responses consistent with project response/error format.
- Use accurate HTTP status codes (`200`, `201`, `400`, `401`, `403`, `404`, `409`, `500`).
- Add/maintain docs when behavior or contracts change.
- Do not over-engineer; optimize for clarity and correctness.
